args: We are the elite of the great Empire,\nand we shall lay low the prince who\nhas so wronged our great leader!
You come from the direction of the\nHalidom, stranger. If you are in league\nwith the prince, you'll find no mercy he—
Hnngh... What's wrong with me?!\nI feel...light-headed...
Everyone's wounds have been treated,\nincluding the spellwyrm—who was beat\nall to heck, lemme tell you.
Thank you, Lea. And you, Emma.

A moment, Prince. The Forte I challenged
in the arena was a knight of pure valor.
I cannot believe she would attack us
in such a fashion.
I sensed something amiss with her mana.\nIt was almost like...
You're on the right track indeed, dearie.\nWhen I took a look at that there dragon,\nI found traces of black mana.
Poor critter was probably possessed by it.\nStill, it likely has some sort of natural\nresistance, as it managed to fight it off.
But if this Lord of the Skies character\nwent and got herself possessed\nin much the same way...
Oh man, that's IT! Forte's gone all cuckoo\nbananas because of black mana!
That savage feeling I got from her\nWAS just like a possessed dragon...
If so, we need to free her.

If we fight her until she uses up all the
black mana, that would likely do it...
But we'll need to be fully prepared to take
her on.
Make it fast. The longer that gunk kicks\naround inside her, the less likely she is\nto recover from it.
Then I'm going to track her down.\nPrince, make your people ready to fight!
I seek to crush everything...\nTo smash... Eradicate...
...But what do I seek after that?
If you pursued me, you truly must\nharbor a wish for death.
In the contrary—I came here to save you.
You are both considerable irritants.\nBut no matter—if you wish to continue\npeddling your nonsense, do so in hell!
Hrk! Mmm, that was a powerful attack—\nand yet, there was nothing in its core.
Your assault in the arena was magnificent.
It was filled with pride in your strength,\nas well as the dignity of a true warrior.
But that attack just now was hollow.\nMeaningless. ...Wind.

You're no better than a highwayman
preying on passersby. Without dignity,
your strength is but a cudgel wielded
by a mewling babe.
You mock YOURSELF, Forte!\nYou have allowed yourself to\nbe consumed by black mana!
Is that all the self-respect you have?!\nIs there no more to the Lord of the Skies?!
Are you back to normal yet?
Tsk. That will not do—not when my brother\nhas demonstrated a keen interest in you.
Okay, where's all this black mana\neven COMING from?!
I will...crush everything. That is...\nthe meaning of my existence...
My lance shall run the pathetic\ndragonblood prince through!
I won't...let you do this...\nFor your sake...and his!

Yes, well, I used even more powerful black
mana than last time, so the darkness of
chaos is going to eat away at her mind
and soul until nothing is left.
Who are these women?\nWere they set upon by fiends?
Captain, I know this lady knight!\nShe turned against us, and is now known\nas the fiend-hating rebel.
And the other is an ally of the Halidom,\nit seems. Interesting...
Sir, should we arrest them and\ntake them to the capital to face\nthe judgment of our Empress?
No. We should not. I've thought of a far\nbetter use for them... Heh heh heh!
